gomodel:SYNGO_2129  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Co-localizes with acetylcholine receptors (AChRs) in mouse NMJ, fluorescence imaging + fig4. Rabsyn is surface expressed, can be deleted/rescued by mutation of AChR interacting domain in myoblasts.\n\n\"Altogether, these results strongly suggest that AChRs serve as a mediator for the targeting and association of rapsyn with the postsynaptic membrane at synaptic sites.\". Experimental description: PMID:11087759 from Jonathan Cohen's group appears to be the source for the Rapsyn-EGFP constructs. This paper mentions the construct is based on mouse species.\n\nthe cultures were also based on mouse species;\n\"MICE, MUSCLE DENERVATION, PLASMID ELECTROPORATION, ACHR LABELING, AND NMJ IMAGING. In this study, female non-Swiss albino mice (6-10 weeks old, 20-30 g) were used.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2129" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
